values: 同意；批准；允许；提供；给予；准予；授予；（勉强）承认
（政府等发给的）拨款；补助金；资助；（政府给予的）土地；授与物；（Grant）格朗；格兰特（人名）

pos_mean_info_list.mean: 出让方；出让人；授与者；转让者

word_mean_info__list.difference: 通常指授予称号或学位等。
指正式地给予或授予，通常伴有仪式进行。
指捐赠大量的钱作基金，也可指给予非物质的东西。
多指出于慷慨、怜悯或正义感而给予，并且通常是在被请求下给予。
最普通用词，泛指将自己的东西给予他人，所给予的东西，物质或非物质的均可。
通常暗示所给予的东西是接受者应得的，而且给予者往往是具有裁判权力的。
侧重所给予的是应得的或是恰当的，或是因某种原因而适于接受的。
正式用词，指把某物作为礼物赠送于某人，也可作引申用。

bilingual.source: The administrator can grant permissions to new users.
bilingual.target: 管理员可以授予新用户权限。

bilingual.source: The court decided to grant guardianship to the mother.
bilingual.target: 法院决定将监护权授予母亲。

bilingual.source: The sharer of the document needs to grant access to everyone.
bilingual.target: 这个文件的分享者需要授予每个人访问权限。

bilingual.source: Our policy is not to grant exclusivity.
bilingual.target: 我们的方针是不授予专卖权.

bilingual.source: These universities are entitled to grant degrees.
bilingual.target: 这些大学有权授予学位。

bilingual.source: Grant an application access to external domains.
bilingual.target: 授予应用程序访问到外部域。

bilingual.source: Do you wish to grant the requested access?
bilingual.target: 您想要授予所请求的访问权限吗?。

bilingual.source: Visa exemption does not grant the right to work.
bilingual.target: 豁免签证并不授予工作的权利.

bilingual.source: Nobel usually does not grant a deceased person.
bilingual.target: 诺贝尔奖通常并不授予已故人士。

list.abstract: GRANT 允许对象的创建者给某用户或某组或所有用户（PUBLIC）某些特定的权限。对象创建后，除了创建者外，除非创建者赋予（GRANT）权限，其他人没有访问对象的权限。一旦用户有某对象的权限，他就可以使用那个特权。 不需要给创建者赋予（GRANT）对象的权限，创建者自动拥有对象的所有权限，包括删除它的权限。
grant，英语单词，作动词时译为“（合法地）授予，允许；（勉强）承认，同意”，作名词时译为“（政府）拨款，补助金；授予，给予；合法转让，正式授予”。

yingyinNormal.en: It does not grant citizenship, or the right to stay here permanently or offer the same benefits that citizens receive.
yingyinNormal.zh: 它不涉及授予国籍，给予永久在此的权力，或者提供正式公民拥有的相同的福利。

yingyinNormal.en: Come. I will grant you the fel.
yingyinNormal.zh: 来吧，我将赐予你魔能。

yingyinNormal.en: We got the grant. Three years, all expenses paid.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们已申请到奖助金，全额赞助我们三年。

yingyinNormal.en: And Ben Grant, founder of Pollyhop. I saw the webcast.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还有本·格兰特，波利跳的创始人。我看到网络直播了。

yingyinNormal.en: You're working on a grant proposal for a new fusion reactor. I'm working on a grant proposal for a new fusion reactor.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你在申请基金研究关于聚变反应堆，我也在申请基金研究关于聚变反应堆。

yingyinNormal.en: Yes, Jeffrey Grant, the guy on trial. He was in here.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对，杰弗里·格兰特，那个正在受审的家伙，他那晚在这儿。

yingyinNormal.en: When Jeffrey Grant started shooting, he tried to, take the gun.
yingyinNormal.zh: 杰弗里·格兰特开枪时，他试图夺下手枪。

yingyinNormal.en: You don't grant birthday wishes, do you? I'm a priest, not a genie.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你不能实现生日愿望的，是吗？我是神父，不是鬼怪。

yingyinNormal.en: Jeffrey Grant's card key has him entering his dorm room at 7:49 P.M.
yingyinNormal.zh: 杰弗里·格兰特在7点49分刷卡，进入宿舍。

yingyinNormal.en: The S.A. is looking for a scapegoat in the Jeffrey Grant prosecution.
yingyinNormal.zh: 州检察官在为杰弗里·格兰特的起诉找替罪羊。

yingyinNormal.en: The National Science Foundation wants to give me a substantial grant.
yingyinNormal.zh: 国家科学基金会要给我一大笔奖金。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, I was... Anyway, look. I definitely did not apply for your grant.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对，我是……随便了，那个，我绝对没申请过你的基金。

yingyinNormal.en: I mean, what is immortality? In time, even Grant's vision will get old.
yingyinNormal.zh: 永生究竟是什么？过个几十年格兰特的设想也会过时。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, he has an election coming up and this Grant issue could haunt him.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他即将面临选举，而这个格兰特案可能会把他拉下马。

yingyinNormal.en: How do I know that Mr. Grant did this? There were no video cameras there.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我怎么知道是格兰特先生做的呢？那里没有摄像头。

yingyinNormal.en: And as my wife, I think you should grant me this favor. We did make vows.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而身为我的老婆，你应该帮我这个忙，我们发过誓了。

yingyinNormal.en: Grant me the fel in front of them, let them see how much stronger I become.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在他们面前赐予我魔能，让他们看到... 我将变得多么的强壮。

yingyinNormal.en: Mr. Grant tried to rape Dani Littlejohn and when she resisted, he killed her.
yingyinNormal.zh: 格兰特先生试图强奸达妮·利特约翰她奋力反抗，于是被其杀害。

yingyinNormal.en: We'd love to, Your Honor, but we're rearresting Mr. Grant on a murder charge.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们愿意，法官阁下，但是我们以谋杀指控再次逮捕格兰特先生。

yingyinNormal.en: Jeffrey Grant was a tragedy. We had an ASA who was looking to make his bones.
yingyinNormal.zh: 杰弗里·格兰特案是个悲剧，我们有个想崭露头角的助理州检察官。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: a sum of money given by an organization, especially a government, for a particular purposes

examination_example.sentence_trans: 更新经济适用住房补助计划。

examination_example.sentence: 5bn programme of <highlight>grants</highlight> to fund new affordable housing, set to expire in 2015, is unlikely to be extended beyond then.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 用于自住新建经济适用房的50亿拨款计划将于2015年到期，但此后不太可能再延长。

examination_example.sentence: The housing sector needs to accept that we are very unlikely to ever return to the era of large-scale public <highlight>grants</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 住房部门需要承认，我们不太可能回到大规模公共拨款的时代。

sense_info_list.en: agree to give or allow something requested to

examination_example.sentence: International tax rules do not <highlight>grant</highlight> them that right.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 国际税收规则并没有赋予他们这种权利。

examination_example.sentence: When he feels down — say, after giving a bad lecture — he <highlight>grants</highlight> himself permission to be human.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当他感到情绪低落时——比如说，在做了一次糟糕的演讲之后——他宽慰自己这是人之常情。

examination_example.sentence: At first glance this might seem like a strength that <highlight>grants</highlight> the ability to make judgments which are unbiased by external factors.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 乍看之下，这似乎是一种力量，它赋予人们做出不受外部因素影响的判断的能力。

sense_info_list.en: accept that something is true, often before expressing an opposite opinion

word_usage.usage: grant是双宾语动词，表达“授予、同意给某人某物”可以说grant sth. to sb.或grant sb. sth.

sense_info_list.en: a sum of money given by an organization; especially a government; for a particular purposes

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Grant</highlight> awarders tend to favor researchers already recognized in their respective fields.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 资助人倾向于支持在各自领域已经得到认可的研究人员。

examination_example.sentence: He said the people who should be paying regard to the Wang paper are the funding agents who distribute government <highlight>grant</highlight> money.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他说，应该关注王教授论文的人是发放政府补助金的资金代理人。

examination_example.sentence: In the competitive game of biomedical science, research has been done on scientists who narrowly lost or won <highlight>grant</highlight> money.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在生物医学的竞争游戏中，研究的对象都是那些以微弱劣势输掉或赢得资助的科学家。

sense_info_list.en: accept that something is true; often before expressing an opposite opinion

examination_example.sentence: The medical community also takes aging for <highlight>granted</highlight>, and can do nothing about it except keep people within a certain health range.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 医学界也认为衰老是理所当然的，除了让人们保持在一定的健康范围内之外，他们对此无能为力。

examination_example.sentence: Most roads, bridges, transit, water systems, the electric grid, and communications networks were installed 50 to 100 years ago, and they are largely taken for <highlight>granted</highlight> until they fail.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大多数道路、桥梁、交通、排水设施、电力网络以及通信设施都是50年前甚至100年前配置的，它们理所当然会被用到不能使用。

sense_info_list.en: agree to give or allow something requested to

examination_example.sentence: Italy boasts more UNESCO World Heritage Sites than any other country in the world, <highlight>granting</highlight> it considerable power and influence within the organization.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相比较世界上任何一个国家，意大利所拥有的联合国教科文组织(UNESCO)世界遗产最多，这使它在该组织中拥有相当大的权力和影响力。
